CopperlineOS drivers — licensing overview

Copyright (c) 2025 CopperlineOS Authors

This repository contains both Linux kernel modules and userspace code.

LICENSE BY DIRECTORY
--------------------
- kernel/           -> GPL-2.0-only
- uapi/             -> Apache-2.0 OR MIT
- userspace/        -> Apache-2.0 OR MIT
- dkms/, udev/, systemd/, tools/, scripts/ -> Apache-2.0 OR MIT

The full texts are provided in:
- LICENSE-GPL-2.0   (GNU General Public License v2.0, “only”)
- LICENSE-APACHE    (Apache License, Version 2.0)
- LICENSE-MIT       (MIT License)

You may use the userspace parts under **either** Apache-2.0 **or** MIT, at your option.
Kernel modules are GPL-2.0-only and include `MODULE_LICENSE("GPL")` for kernel compliance.

SPDX HEADERS (put these at the top of files)
--------------------------------------------
- Kernel C files (modules):
  // SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0-only
  MODULE_LICENSE("GPL");

- UAPI headers and userspace C/Rust/Shell:
  // SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 OR MIT

NOTES
-----
- Distributors must keep the chosen license text with binaries (Apache users keep NOTICE).
- If you contribute, you agree your changes are licensed the same way as the containing directory.
